## Security Standards

### Input Validation

- Use Zod to validate all inputs
- Validate data types and ranges
- Sanitize HTML and SQL special characters

### Authentication & Authorization

- JWT Token authentication
- Password encryption with bcrypt
- Sensitive operations require secondary verification

### Security Headers

```typescript
import helmet from 'helmet';

app.use(helmet());
```

### Rate Limiting

```typescript
import rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';

const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 100 // Max 100 requests per IP
});

app.use('/api', limiter);
```

---

## Prohibited Items

- ❌ Do not use `any` type
- ❌ Do not hardcode sensitive information
- ❌ Do not log passwords
- ❌ Do not ignore error handling
- ❌ Do not use synchronous database operations
- ❌ Do not write business logic in controllers
